---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { SITE, GAME } from '../consts';
import PriorityLinks from '../components/PriorityLinks.astro';
import { beginnerPriorityLinks } from '../data/priorityLinks';

const jsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org', '@type': 'BreadcrumbList', itemListElement: [
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 1, name: 'Home', item: SITE.url },
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 2, name: 'Beginner guide', item: new URL('/beginner-guide', SITE.url).href },
  ],
};
---
<Base
  title="Moonlight Peaks Beginner Guide — Everything We Know Before Launch | Moonlight Peaks Wiki & Guide"
  description="A pre-launch beginner guide to Moonlight Peaks: the night-farming loop, vampire powers, the seven families, romance, fishing, potions, and the Nokturna card game."
  path="/beginner-guide"
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
  crumbs={[{ label: 'Beginner guide' }]}
>
  <article class="page">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="eyebrow">Entry · Guide</p>
      <h1>Moonlight Peaks <em>beginner guide</em></h1>
      <p class="intro">
        What we know so far, gathered from the demo and official trailers. On {GAME.releaseLabel}
        this becomes a full day-one walkthrough with exact numbers. Updated {SITE.updated}.
      </p>

      <h2>Start here checklist</h2>
      <ol class="steps">
        <li><strong>Confirm your platform.</strong> Check Steam, Switch, Switch 2, Steam Deck, Mac, and Android support before planning your first save.</li>
        <li><strong>Try the free demo.</strong> Use it to test controls, character creation, fishing, flower arranging, embroidery, and the early tone.</li>
        <li><strong>Learn the night loop.</strong> Moonlight Peaks is a cozy life sim, but the vampire schedule changes how you think about farming.</li>
        <li><strong>Pick a first focus.</strong> Farming, relationships, decorating, fishing, magic, and Nokturna all connect to separate guide clusters.</li>
      </ol>

      <PriorityLinks
        title="Beginner pages to open next"
        note="first-session path"
        links={beginnerPriorityLinks}
      />

      <h2>The core loop</h2>
      <p>
        You inherit a run-down family homestead and rebuild it into a cozy-gothic farm. Days revolve
        around tending <strong>mystical crops</strong>, raising <strong>magical livestock</strong>,
        and using magic — controlled watering cans and spells — to work the land. Unusually for the
        genre, farming leans into the night, which suits your vampire lifestyle.
      </p>

      <h2>What you'll be doing</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Farming & livestock</strong> — grow enchanted crops and raise creatures unique to the town.</li>
        <li><strong>Spells & potions</strong> — study witchcraft to help on the farm and when gathering.</li>
        <li><strong>Fishing & foraging</strong> — classic cozy gathering, with a supernatural twist.</li>
        <li><strong>Cooking</strong> — turn your harvest into meals and brews.</li>
        <li><strong>Embroidery & flower arranging</strong> — slower hobby activities, shown in the demo.</li>
        <li><strong>Nokturna</strong> — collect cards and play the town's favorite game against residents.</li>
        <li><strong>Home design</strong> — decorate a gothic cottage (pick the perfect coffin) and develop your property.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Being a vampire</h2>
      <p>
        Your lineage is a toolkit, not just a theme. You can <strong>shapeshift</strong> — turning
        into a bat to cross town quickly and reach hidden areas — and unlock ancient abilities from
        enhanced senses onward as you progress. There's a mines area to explore, but note there's
        <strong>no combat anywhere</strong>, so it stays cozy. Many residents are supernatural too,
        so you blend right in.
      </p>

      <h2>The town & its people</h2>
      <p>
        Moonlight Peaks is home to seven families across humans and creatures of the night —
        werewolves, witches, mermaids, and more, with Death himself among the notable characters.
        Befriending and romancing them is a central pillar; our
        <a href="/romance">romance & families entry</a> will track every candidate and their gift
        preferences at launch.
      </p>

      <h2>What not to worry about before launch</h2>
      <p>
        Do not chase exact min-max routes yet. Until the full build is available, crop profit,
        gift values, fish spawns, recipe prices, quest rewards, and resident schedules should be
        treated as launch data. The useful pre-launch work is learning the systems and saving the
        right reference pages.
      </p>

      <h2>Best next pages by goal</h2>
      <table class="facts">
        <tr><th>If you want to play day one</th><td><a href="/release-date">Release date</a>, <a href="/demo">demo guide</a>, and <a href="/platforms">platform guide</a></td></tr>
        <tr><th>If you want romance</th><td><a href="/romance">Romance guide</a>, <a href="/characters">characters</a>, and <a href="/characters/saga">Saga</a></td></tr>
        <tr><th>If you want farming</th><td><a href="/farming">Farming guide</a>, <a href="/magic">magic</a>, and <a href="/activities">activities</a></td></tr>
        <tr><th>If you want collecting</th><td><a href="/activities/fishing">fishing</a>, <a href="/activities/foraging">foraging</a>, <a href="/locations">locations</a>, and the <a href="/map">map</a></td></tr>
      </table>

      <div class="callout wip">
        Pre-launch entry. Exact crop prices, fish lists, gift tables, and cheat commands aren't
        knowable until the full game ships on {GAME.releaseLabel} — we'll fill them in fast. Spot
        something to add? Email {SITE.contact}.
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
